<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,310,1423,1449]" box="[189,310,1423,1449]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1423,1449]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1423,1449]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1470,1567]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[380,535,1470,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Bezzia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicornis">
<emphasis box="[380,535,1470,1496]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">B. albicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from that species in having a scutellum with 4 large setae; parameres swollen on proximal portion, without lateral ribs, with 2 distinct apical lobes; apex of median process of aedeagus strongly bent and gonocoxite with 3 ventral bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
